Shaking Beef

1 1/2 - 2 lbs filet mignon, fat trimmed and cut into 1 1/4" cubes
1 tsp ground black pepper
1 c thinly sliced red onion, preferably spring onions
3 stalks green onion, trimmed and cut to 1" lengths
1 tbsp chopped garlic
2 tbsp unsalted butter

Stir Fry Sauce:
2 tbsp white vinegar
1/4 c white granulated sugar
1/4 c light soy sauce
1/4 c fish sauce
1 tsp cooking rice wine

Salt and Pepper Dipping Sauce:
1 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp freshly ground black pepper
1/4 c of freshly squeezed lime juice
1 bunch watercress, washed

Marinate meat 1/2 tsp black pepper and 1 tbsp oil for ~2hrs. Meanwhile, make the stir-fry sayce by combining all ingredients and mix until sugar is dissolved. Set aside. Divide the meat into 2 portions, and do the same with the onions. Heat 1/4 c of oil in work or large saute pan over maximum heat. Don't overcrowd the pan, may need to do batches. When the oil begins to smoke, add the first batch of meat in one layer. Let a brown crust form, and turn to brown the other side, ~3-4 min. Add red onion, scallions, and garlic to the pan. Shake or stir ingredients in the pan for ~30s. Add stir-fry sauce. Continue to shake or stir ingredients. Add butter, and continue to cook and shake pan until butter melts. Remove from heat. Wash pan and cook next batch. Make lime dipping sauce by mixing together salt and pepper in aramekin. Pour lime juice over salt pepper mixture. Serve beef over watercress with lime dipping sauce.
